\contentsline {added}{Added~(rt): \truncate {\Changestruncatewidth }{Our study considers full 3-DOF in-plane needle manipulation (i.e. $\mathbf {u}=[b_x, b_y, b_k]$) at the needle base, therefore out-of-plane error cannot be eliminated. The simulation-driven strategy can be extended to 3D with a pairing 3D simulator and a 6-DOF needle driver by running input disturbances through the simulator (i.e.~\cref {eq:chap-3-discrete-system}); however, needle shape feedback strategy using FBG needs additional development to account for temperature compensation and shape reconstruction. Our current study only considers manipulation of symmetric-tip needles, therefore needle axial/torsional DOF is not needed due to symmetric tissue force applied to the needle; this DOF is needed when a bevel-tip needle is used since a curved trajectory can be generated due to asymmetric tip forces, and analysis of bevel-tip needle manipulation is comprehensively provided in~\cref {chap:chap-4,chap:chap-5}.}}{82}{section*.68}%
